<br>
Example: The day I got the spell, I leved' up, found my friend in LoIO who was begging me to do some research for him. I grouped with him, so he could see my failure messages (Not that I got them, anyway) He said &quot;okay&quot; and procedded to Med (Looking at the book, twas before the Change)<br>
I say, I will be right back, you don't have all the components for the 29 Earth, and said that a friend of mine has them at one of the BG camps.<br>
<br>
He remained medding as I ran off, lev'd high over the lake, and switched my views so I was pulled back far away so I could see the lake underneath me. I casted CoH, and after 12 seconds, he dropped like a stone, sitting, into the water below.<br>
<br>
Thankfully, he had just gotten Summon:Waterstone the day before, and enjoyed playing with it and always having EB up. When he was finished medding, he stood up to see he was at the bottom of the lake, in the middle. I pulled him back to the shore, we had a good laugh, and someone shouted that the Chancellor was up. I ran in and helped a guildie of mine clear and kill the Chancellor, then I had a demonic Idea. I summoned my friend into the Room and he struggled to get out, but we finnaly got the mobs off him long enough to gate. It was hillarious, to say the least.<br>
<br>
Now, My question is this: If one were to say, get someone foolish enough to join your group in say.. Dreadlands, and you were to levitate over the ruined city under the Combine Spires, and pulled them to your position, not leve'd of course, what would Verant say? Yes, I am evil. ^_^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=brayns>Brayns</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(6/17/02 2:43:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1360.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If summons could kill...</span><hr size=1> Niesei---Just goto lavastorm and lev over top of the big lava pit (the one that annoying monk epic mob sit in), summon them and watch them get BURNED. If they get close to getting out summon them again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umanchyman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>manchyman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#333333>(6/17/02 3:41:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1360.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If summons could kill...</span><hr size=1> I like to move far away from a groupmate then<br>
